    {
      "id": "kpi-highlights",
      "kind": "insights-blue",
      "title": "KPI Highlights & Business Implications",
      "subtitle": "",
      "bullets": [
        "Conversion Rate Improved: Conversion rate increased +9.6% (0.12% to 0.13%). Click volume decreased -19.7% (-10,314,194) while sales decreased -12.0% (-7,422), indicating a more efficient sales-to-click mix than in the prior year.",
        "Sales Volume Pressure: Total sales decreased -12.0% (-7,422). Click volume decreased -19.7% (-10,314,194). Largest declines came from VoucherCodes (-14.4%).",
        "AOV Growth Partially Offsetting Sales Decline: AOV increased +11.1% (£397.01 to £441.26). Total order value decreased -2.2% (-£532,425). Higher basket value only partly offset lower transaction volume. AOV uplift was concentrated in a smaller set of higher-value publishers.",
        "Rising CPA: CPA increased +9.7% (£15.09 to £16.55). Publisher commission changed -3.5% (-£32,374) year-over-year, so each conversion carried a higher acquisition cost.",
        "ROI Improved: ROI increased +1.3% (26.31 to 26.66). For every unit of commission in the current period, programme return moved from 26.31 to 26.66, showing improved spend efficiency."
      ],
